# CC PROMPT — v2.35.4 — feat(agents): runbook-based TRIAGE injection + UI editor (augment mode default)

## What this does

Introduces runbook-based TRIAGE. Playbooks (KAFKA TRIAGE, OVERLAY
DIAGNOSIS, CONTAINER INTROSPECT FIRST, etc.) move from hardcoded prompt
text into DB-stored runbooks. Classifier selects the matching runbook
by keyword match against task text. System prompt gains an
`═══ ACTIVE RUNBOOK ═══` section with the runbook body.

Rollout is staged via `runbookInjectionMode` setting: off / augment /
replace / replace+shrink. Default for v2.35.4: **augment** — the
runbook body is added AFTER the existing prompt section, not replacing
it. This lets us A/B compare via trace diffs before committing to
replacement.

Version bump: 2.35.3 → 2.35.4 (new subsystem, agent hot path, UI).

Design ref: `cc_prompts/PHASE_v2.35_SPEC.md` → "Runbook-based TRIAGE —
augment-first rollout".

